Mechel, RusHydro, Rosneft Shares: Russian Equity Preview

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-06-15T20:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-15/mechel-rushydro-rosneft-shares-russian-equity-preview.html
The following companies may be
active in Russian trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses and
share prices are from the previous close of trading in Moscow.  The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  fell 0.2 percent to 1,678.82. The
dollar-denominated RTS Index slid 0.3 percent to 1,919.05.  OAO  Mechel (MTLR)  : The Russian coal and steel producer
reported the temporary halt of operations at the Sibirginskaya
mine, owned by Southern Kuzbass Coal Co., part of Mechel. The
company said a “heightened level” of fire gases was detected.
The shares slid 1.1 percent to 746.8 rubles.  OAO RusHydro (HYDR RX): Russia’s biggest producer of
renewable energy said it signed a cooperation agreement with
Iceland’s Reykjavik Geothermal to work together on geothermal
power projects. Its stock slipped 1.4 percent to 1.38 rubles.  OAO Rosneft (ROSN RX): Crude oil for July delivery fell in
 New York .  Russia ’s biggest oil producer dropped 1 percent to
245.92 rubles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
